## ✅ Verification checklist

After install or upgrade:

- [ ] `sudo systemctl is-active stremio-addarr` returns `active`.
- [ ] `curl -fsS http://127.0.0.1:7010/healthz | python3 -m json.tool` reports `"ok": true`.
- [ ] `curl -fsS http://127.0.0.1:7010/status.json | python3 -m json.tool` shows the expected release version and reachable Arr services.
- [ ] The exact protected manifest URL printed by `quick.sh` returns JSON, for example: `curl -fsS "https://YOUR_HOSTNAME/YOUR_ADDON_ACCESS_TOKEN/manifest.json" | python3 -m json.tool`.
- [ ] The token-derived Configure URL loads when the UI is enabled: `https://YOUR_HOSTNAME/YOUR_ADDON_ACCESS_TOKEN/configure`.
- [ ] Stremio installs or refreshes the add-on from the protected manifest URL.

When a check fails, use [docs/TROUBLESHOOTING.md](https://github.com/${REPO}/blob/${TAG}/docs/TROUBLESHOOTING.md) rather than retrying with the obsolete unprotected route.
